claim.claim-text:
5. A back-end process for fabricating MEMS devices with fluorosurfactant lubricated micro-machined parts, comprising the steps of: 
fabricating a wafer of said MEMS devices; 
partially sawing said wafer of said MEMS devices; 
testing said wafer of said partially sawn MEMS devices; 
completing sawing said wafer of said MEMS devices; 
packaging operable devices from said sawn wafer of MEMS devices; 
lubricating all surfaces of said packaged MEMS devices by applying a nebulized fluorosurfactant to said surfaces, wherein said fluorosurfactant contains a water-like hydrophillic chain attached to a hydrophobic fluorocarbon; and 
attaching a lid to said package.

9. A MEMS device operable for modulating light having fluorosurfactant lubricated moving parts, comprising: 
a silicon substrate consisting of an array of CMOS memory circuits; 
a planarized thick oxide isolation layer deposited on top of said substrate; 
metal yoke address electrodes and landing pads fabricated over said planarized isolation layer; 
a rotating yoke assembly attached to thin metal torsion hinges, said hinges supported by hinge posts extending above said landing pad metal; 
mirror address electrodes attached to top of additional posts extending above said yoke address pads; and 
highly reflectively metal mirrors mounted to mirror posts attached to and extending above said rotating yoke assembly, wherein 
all surfaces of said MEMS device are lubricated to prevent sticking by means of a fluorosurfactant nebulization, said fluorosurfactant containing a water-like hydrophillic chain attached to a hydrophobic fluorocarbon.

13. A projection display system using a MEMS spatial light modulator with fluorosurfactant lubricated moving parts to prevent sticking of said parts, comprising: 
a light source for producing a beam of light along a first light path; 
light condensing optics in said first light path for focusing said light on to the surface of said MEMS spatial light modulator; 
said MEMS spatial light modulator receiving said focused light from said condensing optics, said light being modulated on a pixel-by-pixel basis and reflected off said spatial light modulator surface; 
control electronics for receiving image data and controlling the modulation of said light focused on to the surface of said MEMS spatial light modulator; 
light reflected off said MEMS spatial light modulator's binary-ON pixels being reflected along a second light path; 
a projection lens inserted in said second light path; 
a projection viewing screen receiving light from said projection lens in said second light path to form of a visible image; 
light reflected off said spatial light modulator's binary-OFF pixels being reflected along a third light path; 
a light trap for receiving and discarding reflected light along said third light path; and 
the moving parts of said light modulator being lubricating with a fluorosurfactant.

14. The display system of claim 13, wherein said MEMS spatial light modulator further comprises: 
a silicon substrate having a digital memory array; 
a planarized oxide isolation layer attached to the top of said memory array; 
a metal yoke address electrode and landing pad layer attached to the top of said oxide layer, metal yoke and hinge assemblies suspended by posts above said address electrodes on landing pad layer by means of metal posts; 
metal mirror address electrodes extended on posts above said yoke address electrodes; and 
metal mirrors attached to said yokes by means of metal mirror posts.
